This file describes required resources and installation instructions.


Required resources
------------------

1) gcc and gmake to compile a whole system

2) nkf (network kanji filter) and jperl (perl patched for Japanese)
	to compile dictionary-database 

3) JUMAN (ftp://pine.kyoto-u.ac.jp/pub/juman/juman3.2.tar.gz)

4) Bunrui Goi Hyou (Word List by Semantic Principles)
	A FD version is available (3,500yen) from
		Dai Nippon Tosho 
	        Tel. +81-03-3561-8679

5) EDR Japanese Word Dictionary (http://www.iijnet.or.jp/edr)

6) IPA Lexicon, called IPAL (see ftp://ftp.mgt.ipa.go.jp/pub/ipal/README.E)

(You can run the parser without these dictionaries tentatively.)


Installation instructions
-------------------------

1) set the following variables in "knp2.0b3/system/Makefile" and 
	"knp2.0b3/dict/Makefile".
	
	KNP_DIR
	JUMANLIB
        RCPATH
	BGH_FILE
	EDR_FILE
	IPALV1_FILE
	IPALV2_FILE
	IPALA1_FILE
	IPALA2_FILE
	IPALN_DIR

2) do `gmake all' to compile a parsing program and dictionary-database
	(it takes quite a long time to compile the database.)

